WEBVTT

00:11.666 --> 00:13.737
NOAH:
Yeah, of course.

00:13.737 --> 00:16.050
Okay.
Tim, you nutter.

00:16.050 --> 00:17.776
To what do I owe the pleasure?

00:19.364 --> 00:22.401
Uh...yeah, I've got five.
Yeah, I've got five minutes.

00:22.401 --> 00:23.609
I'm gonna go upstairs
for something.

00:23.609 --> 00:24.645
Okay.

00:26.405 --> 00:28.166
NOAH:
Yep, okay.

00:29.029 --> 00:31.272
[ Buttons clicking ]

00:45.217 --> 00:47.116
I broke my leg when I was a kid.

00:47.116 --> 00:49.842
All my friends signed my cast.

00:51.292 --> 00:53.087
It was kind of great.

00:53.087 --> 00:56.194
Sometimes I fantasize
about it happening again.

00:56.194 --> 00:58.472
I'd get a few weeks off work.

00:58.472 --> 01:01.751
Watch some box sets.
Learn a language.

01:01.751 --> 01:04.961
I suppose I'm saying you should
see this as an opportunity.

01:07.860 --> 01:10.070
When people ask, what do you
want me to tell them?

01:11.657 --> 01:13.659
Say you broke your leg at work?

01:18.526 --> 01:19.700
Did you see that?

01:25.119 --> 01:26.914
It's probably a prank.

01:26.914 --> 01:29.296
-It's stealing.
-So phone the police.

01:29.296 --> 01:30.504
MIKE:
Yeah, I will.

01:30.504 --> 01:31.781
[ Mug thuds ]

01:34.197 --> 01:37.269
You know, last week I was
investigating a kidnapping.

01:37.925 --> 01:39.513
Now look at me.

01:39.513 --> 01:41.756
I'm calling in
a stolen garden gnome.

01:43.137 --> 01:45.312
This is gonna be tough.

01:45.312 --> 01:48.349
No work.
Just you and your thoughts.

01:48.349 --> 01:49.971
Try not to dwell on them.

01:49.971 --> 01:51.904
Find something
to keep yourself busy.

01:53.734 --> 01:55.460
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

01:55.460 --> 01:56.909
Okay.

01:56.909 --> 01:58.152
Have a good day.
I love you.

01:58.152 --> 02:00.050
See you later.

02:00.050 --> 02:02.294
Bye.

02:02.294 --> 02:03.606
[ Door closes ]

02:12.684 --> 02:15.514
♪ There once was a place
with my little lovely ♪

02:15.514 --> 02:17.758
♪ Whey, hey, ho ♪

02:17.758 --> 02:21.417
♪ And I seek and I search,
and I know that I'll find it ♪

02:21.417 --> 02:23.591
♪ Whey, hey, ho ♪

02:23.591 --> 02:26.284
♪ I know the wind, she blows ♪

02:26.284 --> 02:31.358
♪ I know the tides are low ♪

02:31.358 --> 02:37.191
♪ But you'll find me
at the Whitepost ♪

02:37.191 --> 02:42.196
♪ You'll find me
at the Whitepost ♪

02:44.923 --> 02:47.719
[ Birds squawking ]

02:47.719 --> 02:48.823
[ Sighs ]

02:51.240 --> 02:52.586
I'm gonna kill him.

02:52.586 --> 02:54.519
Have you thought
about couples therapy?

02:54.519 --> 02:56.762
Nah, I'm gonna
chop his balls off.

02:56.762 --> 02:58.626
Alright. Well, before
you do that, Kelly,

02:58.626 --> 03:00.456
why don't you tell me
why you think he's cheating?

03:02.320 --> 03:03.838
I go to bed early.

03:03.838 --> 03:06.669
When he thinks I'm asleep
he creeps out.

03:06.669 --> 03:08.395
Doesn't come back
till the early hours.

03:09.189 --> 03:11.225
Have you tried talking to him?

03:11.225 --> 03:13.193
I mean, why don't you ask him
where he's going?

03:13.193 --> 03:15.195
I don't want him
to think I'm paranoid.

03:16.541 --> 03:18.439
We've only just
moved in together.

03:19.923 --> 03:21.753
I'm keeping the crazy in.

03:22.409 --> 03:24.480
Okay, well, um...

03:24.480 --> 03:26.067
I'll follow him, then,
see where he's going.

03:26.067 --> 03:29.243
But only if you're really sure
you wanna know.

03:29.243 --> 03:31.418
KELLY: Stuart said he hit
the jackpot when he met me.

03:31.418 --> 03:33.834
I thought the same thing.

03:33.834 --> 03:35.422
I don't wanna kill him.
I love him.

03:35.422 --> 03:37.907
But if he's cheating on me
[Exhales deeply]

03:37.907 --> 03:41.393
I swear to God, I'm gonna kick
his lovely little head in.

03:44.224 --> 03:45.880
[ Mike slurps ]

03:51.058 --> 03:53.647
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:55.476 --> 03:57.616
[ Indistinct talking ]

04:24.850 --> 04:27.888
[ Thunder crashes ]

04:27.888 --> 04:30.649
[ Rain falling ]

04:30.649 --> 04:32.651
[ Man shouts ]

04:38.623 --> 04:41.522
[ Banging on window ]

04:44.767 --> 04:46.458
[ Indistinct shouting ]

05:02.681 --> 05:04.338
[ Line ringing ]

05:04.338 --> 05:05.374
OPERATOR:
Which service do you require?

05:05.374 --> 05:06.375
Police, please.

05:16.902 --> 05:19.802
[ Thunder rumbling ]

05:21.182 --> 05:23.564
[ Doorbell rings ]

05:41.168 --> 05:43.377
[ Buzzer ]

06:24.176 --> 06:26.040
Nikki, I know what I saw.

06:26.040 --> 06:28.008
He suffers from night terrors.

06:28.008 --> 06:31.977
He sees giant spiders and
hooded assassins in his sleep.

06:31.977 --> 06:33.496
His eyes were wide open.

06:33.496 --> 06:36.568
His eyes remain open
during the night terror.

06:36.568 --> 06:38.777
He can move around, talk.

06:38.777 --> 06:41.470
Sometimes he can be violent.
But he is still asleep.

06:41.470 --> 06:44.438
-And he's got no memory of it?
-NIKKI: His wife backed him up.

06:44.438 --> 06:45.957
She knows how to reassure him.

06:45.957 --> 06:47.268
They've got it
all under control.

06:47.268 --> 06:48.787
Maybe they should try
sleeping pills?

06:48.787 --> 06:50.858
NIKKI: They don't believe
in medicating the problem.

06:50.858 --> 06:53.413
I said there's something
called wasting police time.

06:53.413 --> 06:54.966
And I don't believe in that.

06:56.001 --> 06:58.072
Uh, you telling them or me?

06:58.072 --> 06:59.488
Both.

06:59.488 --> 07:01.835
Please, stop snooping
on your neighbors.

07:04.872 --> 07:06.633
Just enjoy your time off.

07:08.013 --> 07:09.843
See you later.

07:13.571 --> 07:15.227
[ Door opens ]

07:16.988 --> 07:17.989
[ Door closes ]

07:58.063 --> 08:00.169
[ Rain falling ]

08:13.493 --> 08:14.632
You didn't have to come,
you know.

08:14.632 --> 08:15.840
It might be a long night.

08:15.840 --> 08:17.876
What if he's not just a cheat?

08:17.876 --> 08:19.360
What if he's an ax murderer?

08:20.292 --> 08:21.673
It's my job to look out for you.

08:23.330 --> 08:25.539
Well, say he is an ax murderer.
What are you gonna do?

08:25.539 --> 08:27.886
Put him in detention?

08:27.886 --> 08:29.163
I might.

08:29.163 --> 08:30.924
If he's really disappointed me.

08:30.924 --> 08:32.270
[ Laughs ]

08:35.791 --> 08:37.896
Have you ever cheated on anyone?

08:37.896 --> 08:40.589
Wow.
Direct question.

08:42.556 --> 08:44.558
It's early days
between us, you know.

08:44.558 --> 08:46.077
You're supposed to be
keeping the crazy in.

08:46.077 --> 08:48.804
Oh, I think that ship
has sailed, don't you?

08:48.804 --> 08:50.806
[ Laughs ]

08:50.806 --> 08:51.910
Have you, though?

08:53.187 --> 08:55.120
No, have you?

08:57.847 --> 09:01.817
When I was married,
I got close to someone at work.

09:02.680 --> 09:03.750
PEARL:
A teacher?

09:06.546 --> 09:08.133
Did she lock you
in the maths cupboard?

09:08.133 --> 09:09.928
-Ha ha.
-Take advantage of you.

09:09.928 --> 09:11.309
-It wasn't like that.
-Like what?

09:11.309 --> 09:13.587
-Physical.
-Oh.

09:13.587 --> 09:16.728
We didn't, you know --
we didn't even kiss.

09:16.728 --> 09:18.972
My therapist called it
"emotional infidelity."

09:18.972 --> 09:20.249
Sounds hot.

09:21.388 --> 09:23.321
We shared things.

09:23.321 --> 09:26.635
Hopes. Doubts. Secrets.

09:26.635 --> 09:27.774
There he is.

09:27.774 --> 09:29.465
I'm not proud of it.

09:29.465 --> 09:32.261
Well, give yourself a break.
It sounds like nothing happened.

09:32.261 --> 09:33.331
TOM: Yeah, but it did, though,
didn't it?

09:33.331 --> 09:35.782
It was intense and intimate.

09:35.782 --> 09:37.162
It was just wrong.

09:37.162 --> 09:38.750
-We're gonna follow him.
-TOM: Wait a sec.

09:39.613 --> 09:43.790
I just want you to know
I will never do that again.

09:45.585 --> 09:47.379
I know.

09:48.967 --> 09:51.936
[ Engine starts ]

10:09.332 --> 10:10.989
[ Gearshift clicks ]

10:17.168 --> 10:19.826
TOM: Does it ever get you down,
chasing cheats?

10:21.206 --> 10:22.622
Well, sometimes
you do find evidence

10:22.622 --> 10:24.520
that ends a relationship.

10:24.520 --> 10:26.971
But mostly it's just
a misunderstanding.

10:26.971 --> 10:29.663
And those are the best,
when you save a relationship.

10:29.663 --> 10:33.287
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

10:33.287 --> 10:34.668
PEARL:
Like this time.

10:34.668 --> 10:37.222
Stuart's not a cheat.

10:37.222 --> 10:38.638
He's a trainspotter.

10:40.640 --> 10:41.882
Is that worse?

10:47.163 --> 10:50.097
[ Buzzer ]

10:50.097 --> 10:52.030
[ Doorbell rings ]

11:06.666 --> 11:09.047
[ Buzzer ]

11:34.694 --> 11:36.454
MIKE:
He's cheating on his wife.

11:36.454 --> 11:39.250
-The night terror fella.
-So what?

11:39.250 --> 11:41.114
MIKE: Well, don't you think
it's a little bit suspicious?

11:41.114 --> 11:43.323
It's none of my business.

11:43.323 --> 11:45.083
MIKE: Right, just hear me out,
alright?

11:45.083 --> 11:46.567
Alright, this better be good.

11:46.567 --> 11:49.191
MIKE: First of all,
he stole a unicorn.

11:51.918 --> 11:53.264
Oh, my God.

12:01.721 --> 12:02.860
Ugh.

12:12.973 --> 12:15.596
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

12:46.904 --> 12:48.215
[ Buttons click ]

12:56.292 --> 12:58.122
[ Line ringing ]

13:01.332 --> 13:03.541
-PEARL: Hi.
-MIKE: Pearl. It's me.

13:04.853 --> 13:06.578
I need you to see something.

13:08.235 --> 13:09.616
That's Noah.

13:09.616 --> 13:11.376
-And he has nightmares?
-Night terrors.

13:11.376 --> 13:14.586
He jumps around, screams,
attacks his wife.

13:14.586 --> 13:15.622
All in his sleep.

13:15.622 --> 13:17.037
What, and he has
no memory of it?

13:17.037 --> 13:19.557
Well, so he says.

13:19.557 --> 13:21.145
And that's his wife, Maddie.

13:21.145 --> 13:23.285
She vouched for him
to the police, but...

13:23.285 --> 13:24.804
You're not buying it?

13:24.804 --> 13:26.633
Nah.
And Jimi lives there.

13:26.633 --> 13:28.290
PEARL:
And Jimi's a unicorn?

13:28.290 --> 13:31.051
MIKE: No. Jimi's a DFL.
I'll come back to the unicorn.

13:31.051 --> 13:33.847
Jimi works in the city.
Only comes back at weekends.

13:33.847 --> 13:36.919
Now, he's given Noah a key
so he can go and feed the fish.

13:36.919 --> 13:39.819
Ah, right, but Noah's using it
as a shag pad.

13:39.819 --> 13:40.820
Right.

13:40.820 --> 13:42.856
Well, you've done your research.

13:42.856 --> 13:45.169
How do you know
all your neighbors' names?

13:45.169 --> 13:46.687
Well, I say hello.

13:46.687 --> 13:48.517
Bit of neighborly small talk
every now and then.

13:50.381 --> 13:52.003
Alright.
I avoid them at all costs.

13:52.003 --> 13:54.040
But I'm a detective.
I who my neighbors are.

13:54.040 --> 13:55.593
Alright, that's Grace.

13:55.593 --> 13:58.423
She takes in Jimi's parcels
when he's not there.

13:58.423 --> 14:00.736
Now, Noah, he stole her unicorn.

14:00.736 --> 14:02.842
He just hopped over the fence
and took it.

14:02.842 --> 14:03.843
Right.

14:05.499 --> 14:07.847
Okay, never mind
about the unicorn.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.194
Look.
I took these photos.

14:12.127 --> 14:14.508
I know where this ends.
I've seen it a hundred times.

14:14.508 --> 14:16.062
Abusive husbands
who think they can take out

14:16.062 --> 14:17.615
all their frustrations
on their wives.

14:17.615 --> 14:19.720
-She looks terrified.
-MIKE: Yeah.

14:19.720 --> 14:22.137
And at this stage it's difficult
for the police to intervene,

14:22.137 --> 14:23.207
so I need help.

14:25.278 --> 14:26.693
You in?

14:26.693 --> 14:27.694
Yeah.

14:27.694 --> 14:28.902
Thanks.

14:28.902 --> 14:30.559
Well, you might not thank me

14:30.559 --> 14:32.595
when you find out
what my fees are.

14:33.700 --> 14:35.357
I was thinking we'd have
a trial period.

14:35.357 --> 14:37.877
Well, it's the weekend, innit?
I'm on double time.

14:47.127 --> 14:48.439
[ Door opens ]

14:48.439 --> 14:51.718
-KAT: Hi! It's only me.
-Hey.

14:51.718 --> 14:53.306
Hi, Pearl.
You look nice.

14:53.306 --> 14:54.617
Oh, thanks.

14:54.617 --> 14:55.687
-Hi.
-Hi.

14:57.068 --> 15:02.108
Oh, I, um, went to the shop
and I got you some soups.

15:02.108 --> 15:03.557
It's fuel for your stakeout.

15:03.557 --> 15:05.628
Oh, you didn't have to do that.

15:05.628 --> 15:07.596
You staying?

15:07.596 --> 15:09.770
Saturday night with the Stasi?

15:09.770 --> 15:11.738
-I think I'll pass.
-Right.

15:17.019 --> 15:18.952
It looks like a hotbed
of criminality over there.

15:21.368 --> 15:22.749
Well, I'd say good luck.

15:22.749 --> 15:24.371
But that would mean you're right

15:24.371 --> 15:25.717
and your neighbor is planning
on murdering his wife.

15:25.717 --> 15:27.409
So I hope you're wrong

15:27.409 --> 15:30.481
and that you have a boring
and uneventful evening.

15:30.481 --> 15:31.723
What are you up to?

15:31.723 --> 15:33.070
Karaoke with the girls.

15:33.070 --> 15:35.106
-Oh.
-Oh, yeah, have a good night.

15:35.106 --> 15:37.074
You're gonna join us
when you're better, eh?

15:37.074 --> 15:38.972
Really?
I didn't know you did karaoke.

15:38.972 --> 15:39.973
What's your song?

15:39.973 --> 15:40.974
It's power ballads.

15:40.974 --> 15:43.390
[ Both laugh ]

15:43.390 --> 15:44.495
I'll see you later.

15:44.495 --> 15:46.014
-MIKE: Alright.
-KAT: Bye, Pearl.

15:46.014 --> 15:47.084
-Bye.
-KAT: Love to Tom.

15:47.084 --> 15:48.809
-Yeah. Have fun.
-KAT: Thank you.

15:49.500 --> 15:51.122
-See ya.
-Bye.

15:56.127 --> 15:57.577
She's alright, isn't she,
me being here?

15:57.577 --> 16:00.166
Yeah. Yeah.
Kat's cool.

16:00.166 --> 16:01.961
She knows this is just work.
It's fine.

16:01.961 --> 16:04.377
Yeah.
Of course, yeah.

16:08.588 --> 16:09.623
You hungry?

16:10.762 --> 16:12.764
Yeah.

16:12.764 --> 16:15.422
I could heat those soups up.

16:15.422 --> 16:16.734
Yeah.

16:16.734 --> 16:18.598
Or...

16:18.598 --> 16:19.875
we could get a Chinese?

16:20.980 --> 16:22.567
Yeah, go on.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.989
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:31.749 --> 16:33.440
Pearl stood you up?

16:33.440 --> 16:35.063
She's 'round at Mike's.

16:35.063 --> 16:37.410
Oh, well done, you.

16:37.410 --> 16:39.999
Most people
would feel threatened.

16:39.999 --> 16:41.000
TOM: By Mike?

16:41.000 --> 16:43.416
[ Laughs ]
Nah. Trust me.

16:43.416 --> 16:44.693
Not Pearl's type.

16:44.693 --> 16:47.006
She likes a laugh,
and between us,

16:47.006 --> 16:49.008
Mike's a bit of a Debbie Downer.

16:49.008 --> 16:51.389
Oh, I wouldn't say that.

16:51.389 --> 16:52.908
Would you, Ruby?

16:52.908 --> 16:55.635
I'd say he's more
the strong silent type.

16:55.635 --> 16:57.188
DOLLY: Yes.

16:57.188 --> 16:58.810
Yeah, because he can't
think of any words.

16:58.810 --> 17:01.158
DOLLY: No.
It's -- He's --

17:01.158 --> 17:03.263
-Mysterious.
-That's it.

17:03.263 --> 17:05.748
Strong, silent, mysterious.

17:05.748 --> 17:07.233
-Like James Bond.
-Mm.

17:09.649 --> 17:11.030
This is a wind-up.

17:11.030 --> 17:14.240
Yeah. You got me.
[ Chuckles ]

17:14.240 --> 17:16.380
Mike's not exactly
a catch, is he?

17:16.380 --> 17:17.622
I mean, he's literally lame!

17:20.108 --> 17:23.387
[ As Sean Connery ] James Bond,
licensed to hobble.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.811
I know you don't
wanna talk about it.

17:33.811 --> 17:35.882
But I have gotta ask.

17:35.882 --> 17:38.126
What, my leg?

17:38.126 --> 17:40.473
Was you injured
in the line of duty?

17:40.473 --> 17:42.889
Something like that.

17:42.889 --> 17:45.443
Well, Kat has sworn
the swimming group to secrecy.

17:45.443 --> 17:46.651
Oh, yeah?

17:46.651 --> 17:48.412
Yeah, said it was classified.

17:48.412 --> 17:50.828
Case of national security.
Made you out like a hero.

17:51.898 --> 17:54.280
Well, she can put
a positive spin on anything.

17:54.280 --> 17:55.488
Well, that's a good quality.

17:56.489 --> 17:58.491
I know, just...

18:00.079 --> 18:01.597
We're just different that way.

18:01.597 --> 18:03.910
Uh, yeah.

18:05.325 --> 18:08.087
That's her way of dealing
with everything, you know?

18:10.848 --> 18:13.299
Look forward, not back.

18:16.095 --> 18:17.268
Did she lose her partner, too?

18:21.100 --> 18:22.480
Yeah.

18:23.757 --> 18:24.793
I'm sorry.

18:27.244 --> 18:30.143
Is that what you're doing?
Looking forwards?

18:30.143 --> 18:31.765
Yeah, I'm trying.

18:37.530 --> 18:39.118
Go on, then,
tell me how you did it.

18:39.118 --> 18:41.292
Was it foiling a heist?

18:41.292 --> 18:42.707
Or tackling a terrorist?

18:42.707 --> 18:44.261
I was at work, actually.

18:44.261 --> 18:45.883
-Sort of.
-Okay.

18:49.335 --> 18:50.957
It was the police
five-a-side tournament.

18:50.957 --> 18:52.993
Well, who did it?
Some monster of a cop?

18:54.961 --> 18:55.962
Nikki.

18:55.962 --> 18:58.275
[ Laughs ]

19:33.551 --> 19:34.518
Mike.

19:34.518 --> 19:36.209
Wake up, Mike.
Wake up.

19:36.209 --> 19:37.590
-Hmm?
-PEARL: He's up, look.

19:37.590 --> 19:39.212
He's got a knife.

19:39.212 --> 19:40.317
Look.

19:49.257 --> 19:51.776
Right, we've gotta do something!

19:53.226 --> 19:54.779
-I'm gonna go 'round there.
-No, no, no, no.

19:54.779 --> 19:56.229
-What?
-Wait. I'm calling the police.

19:56.229 --> 19:57.057
-PEARL: Mike!
-Wait.

19:59.198 --> 20:00.371
PEARL: Look.

20:11.037 --> 20:12.556
What was that?

20:13.764 --> 20:15.697
MIKE: I told you.
Something weird's going on.

20:17.008 --> 20:18.389
Is that definitely
a night terror?

20:18.389 --> 20:19.252
What if it wasn't?

20:20.080 --> 20:22.566
-What do you mean?
-MIKE: What if he isn't asleep?

20:22.566 --> 20:23.843
We don't know for sure.

20:23.843 --> 20:25.293
You're saying he's awake?

20:25.293 --> 20:27.467
If he is asleep,
that's odd and dangerous.

20:27.467 --> 20:30.263
If he's awake,
then he's conscious.

20:30.263 --> 20:33.232
And he's thinking
about killing his wife.

20:39.617 --> 20:41.378
[ Buzzer ]

20:47.246 --> 20:49.282
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

20:51.457 --> 20:52.734
MADDIE: Noah!

20:52.734 --> 20:54.425
You forgot your passport.

20:54.425 --> 20:56.462
[ Indistinct talking ]

21:14.756 --> 21:16.930
[ Engine revs ]

21:43.957 --> 21:45.338
Alright.

21:48.203 --> 21:50.309
NOAH:
It's my word against hers.

21:50.309 --> 21:51.724
It's your word
against Mia Adler.

21:51.724 --> 21:53.346
But here's the problem.

21:53.346 --> 21:56.349
Now it's your word
against Clemmie Dixon,

21:56.349 --> 21:57.661
-Rochelle Dorsey.
-NOAH: Yeah, alright.

21:57.661 --> 21:59.939
And they're all saying
the same thing.

21:59.939 --> 22:01.872
That you sexually harassed them.

22:01.872 --> 22:03.736
Well, you're the lawyer.
What are yousaying?

22:03.736 --> 22:06.497
LAWYER: They're going to revoke
your pilot's license, so...

22:06.497 --> 22:07.602
what else do you know how to do?

22:17.197 --> 22:19.407
MIKE: Justice?
What does that mean?

22:19.407 --> 22:21.098
It's all about sexual harassment
in the workplace.

22:21.098 --> 22:22.962
Calling out predators.

22:22.962 --> 22:25.585
So, now he's been sexually
harassing flight attendants.

22:25.585 --> 22:28.105
-Yeah, and he got sacked for it.
-And he hasn't told Maddie.

22:28.105 --> 22:30.003
No. And he dresses up
as a pilot every day

22:30.003 --> 22:31.350
and pretends to go to work.

22:31.350 --> 22:33.421
While really he's next door
with her.

22:33.421 --> 22:34.905
PEARL:
Yeah, and that's Lois.

22:34.905 --> 22:36.458
And she's the only
flight attendant

22:36.458 --> 22:37.735
-that still believes in him.
-MIKE: God knows why.

23:00.724 --> 23:02.139
-[ Buzzer ]
-Oh. Hold on.

23:32.411 --> 23:35.655
[ Indistinct talking ]

23:58.091 --> 23:59.127
[ Scoffs ]

24:01.578 --> 24:02.820
This guy.

24:06.824 --> 24:09.517
[ Buzzer ]

24:09.517 --> 24:11.277
Follow Lois.

24:12.451 --> 24:14.245
-PEARL: On it.
-MIKE: Yeah.

24:15.281 --> 24:17.456
Here you are, spare key so you
can let yourself in and out.

24:17.456 --> 24:18.905
-I'll call you later.
-Alright.

24:18.905 --> 24:20.217
MIKE:
Here, Pearl.

24:20.217 --> 24:21.908
PEARL: Yeah.

24:21.908 --> 24:23.841
You're not bad at this.

24:23.841 --> 24:25.187
I know.

24:25.187 --> 24:26.810
Double time, remember?

24:29.122 --> 24:30.814
[ Door opens ]

24:46.312 --> 24:48.487
Oh, no.

25:18.724 --> 25:20.588
-What are you doing?
-What?

25:20.588 --> 25:22.279
He didn't?

25:22.279 --> 25:23.556
And youdidn't?

25:23.556 --> 25:24.661
What?

25:24.661 --> 25:26.007
'Cause listen, Pearl.

25:26.007 --> 25:27.560
I watched him having lunch
the other day,

25:27.560 --> 25:29.528
and he ate his burger
with a knife and fork.

25:29.528 --> 25:31.322
-Who?
-Tom!

25:31.322 --> 25:33.186
Well, he's got manners!

25:35.361 --> 25:37.950
Oh.
You think because I'm --

25:37.950 --> 25:38.882
[ Laughs ]

25:38.882 --> 25:40.331
Please tell me you're not.

25:40.331 --> 25:42.161
Oh, no.
We are, actually.

25:42.161 --> 25:45.544
Yeah, we're gonna go to Vegas,
dress up as Elvis and Priscilla.

25:45.544 --> 25:46.993
Don't even joke about it.

25:46.993 --> 25:48.374
[ Chuckles ]

25:48.374 --> 25:49.893
And you're not invited!

26:03.769 --> 26:05.356
Yeah, 'course I'm sure.

26:05.356 --> 26:07.358
I mean, she's barley showing,
but she's pregnant.

26:07.358 --> 26:08.567
Noah's the father.

26:08.567 --> 26:09.982
PEARL: Yeah, and they're
getting married.

26:09.982 --> 26:11.984
-Well, Lois thinks they are.
-MIKE: Right.

26:13.986 --> 26:15.194
Mike?

26:15.194 --> 26:17.368
Hang on.
Yeah?

26:17.368 --> 26:18.853
I'm tired.
I'm gonna go to bed.

26:18.853 --> 26:20.026
Alright, yeah.

26:21.372 --> 26:22.960
Pearl, sorry, go on.

26:22.960 --> 26:24.859
PEARL: And I've checked
the deeds for the flat,

26:24.859 --> 26:26.619
and it's in Maddie's name.

26:27.655 --> 26:29.277
MIKE:
And Noah doesn't own the flat.

26:29.277 --> 26:31.244
No, but if she died,
he'd inherit it.

26:31.244 --> 26:33.143
[ Door slams ]

26:33.143 --> 26:34.800
So he's out of work.
He's skint.

26:34.800 --> 26:36.284
He's planning on remarrying.

26:36.284 --> 26:38.010
Yeah, and he's got a kid
on the way.

26:38.010 --> 26:40.806
-MIKE: That's motive.
-Mm.

26:40.806 --> 26:42.324
What are they up to now?

26:42.324 --> 26:44.499
They're arguing.

26:47.640 --> 26:51.023
Jimi's back for the weekend,
struggling with a flat pack.

26:52.887 --> 26:54.613
Grace has been on the vodka.

26:54.613 --> 26:56.028
[ Pearl laughs ]

26:56.028 --> 26:57.995
Maybe she's celebrating
getting her unicorn back.

26:58.755 --> 26:59.756
Poor Jimi.

27:07.626 --> 27:09.179
Night, then.

27:09.179 --> 27:10.801
PEARL:
Yeah, night.

27:11.422 --> 27:14.218
[ Laughter,
indistinct conversation ]

27:38.726 --> 27:41.349
[ Van door opens ]

27:44.110 --> 27:45.318
[ Buzzer ]

27:54.673 --> 27:56.329
[ Buzzer ]

28:13.830 --> 28:15.901
[ Glass shatters ]

28:52.972 --> 28:55.181
[ Birds chirping ]

29:07.193 --> 29:08.816
[ Yawns ]

29:30.458 --> 29:32.667
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

29:46.370 --> 29:47.855
And the blinds have been shut
for a whole day?

29:47.855 --> 29:49.580
And the curtains drawn
the whole time.

29:51.237 --> 29:52.445
And no one's been out?

29:54.482 --> 29:56.622
How bad was this argument?

29:56.622 --> 29:57.830
It was bad.

29:57.830 --> 29:59.245
Smashed plates.
Broken glass.

29:59.245 --> 30:01.661
Noah punched the wall in.

30:01.661 --> 30:03.042
We should call the police.

30:03.042 --> 30:05.424
We do that,
Nikki'll break my other leg.

30:08.427 --> 30:10.015
Something's happened!

30:13.812 --> 30:15.399
I'm -- I'm gonna go over there.

30:15.399 --> 30:17.988
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.
No, Pearl, Pearl, wait!

30:17.988 --> 30:20.094
-Pearl! Pearl!
-[ Door closes ]

30:27.826 --> 30:29.897
[ Buzzer ]

30:33.659 --> 30:35.557
PEARL:
Meter reading.

30:35.557 --> 30:37.697
[ Buzzer ]

30:43.324 --> 30:45.533
[ Sighs ]
Jesus Christ.

30:48.329 --> 30:50.262
[ Doorbell ringing ]

30:52.057 --> 30:53.437
Maddie?

30:53.437 --> 30:55.543
[ Knocking on door ]

31:05.001 --> 31:06.450
Maddie?

31:18.877 --> 31:20.879
No, no, no, no.

31:20.879 --> 31:22.328
Oh, Pearl.

32:13.207 --> 32:15.934
[ Breathing shakily ]

32:18.384 --> 32:20.179
[ Siren chirps ]

32:23.527 --> 32:24.597
[ Vehicle door closes ]

32:24.597 --> 32:26.806
[ Indistinct talking ]

32:38.957 --> 32:40.613
[ Radio chatter ]

32:40.613 --> 32:43.616
[ Vehicle doors close ]

32:43.616 --> 32:45.825
[ Indistinct talking ]

32:57.837 --> 33:00.185
NIKKI: Maddie said she woke up,
Noah was standing over her.

33:00.185 --> 33:01.427
And he was holding
the kitchen knife.

33:01.427 --> 33:02.808
MIKE:
Not for the first time.

33:02.808 --> 33:04.775
Yeah, well, she's still
in shock, obviously,

33:04.775 --> 33:06.225
but she's not sure
what happened next.

33:06.225 --> 33:07.847
It's a bit of a blur.

33:07.847 --> 33:10.057
She thinks it was
a night terror.

33:10.057 --> 33:11.851
He attacks her
with a kitchen knife.

33:11.851 --> 33:14.026
There's a scuffle.
She tries to grab the knife.

33:14.026 --> 33:16.339
And when they're
grappling for it, she stabs him.

33:16.339 --> 33:17.996
So it's self-defense,
an accident.

33:17.996 --> 33:19.549
It's looking that way.

33:19.549 --> 33:20.619
The photos are gonna help.

33:20.619 --> 33:22.793
So, I'm glad you broke your leg.

33:23.829 --> 33:25.624
I don't buy any of this.

33:25.624 --> 33:27.660
He was cheating on her.

33:27.660 --> 33:29.869
His girlfriend was pregnant.
He had motive to kill her.

33:29.869 --> 33:31.388
She said it was a night terror.

33:31.388 --> 33:32.803
She's heartbroken.

33:32.803 --> 33:34.184
I guess we'll never know.

33:34.184 --> 33:36.876
Either way,
you tried to warn me.

33:36.876 --> 33:38.223
And now someone's dead.

33:38.223 --> 33:40.466
-Nikki.
-NIKKI: It's okay.

33:40.466 --> 33:41.847
I'm owning it.

33:45.264 --> 33:48.026
I'm just relieved
it wasn't Maddie, you know?

34:01.591 --> 34:03.455
[ Buzzer ]

34:40.871 --> 34:43.736
[ Buzzer ]

34:43.736 --> 34:44.841
MADDIE: Hello?

34:44.841 --> 34:47.154
Hi, Maddie.
It's Pearl.

34:47.154 --> 34:48.845
I'll buzz you in.

34:48.845 --> 34:50.743
[ Buzzer ]

34:59.269 --> 35:01.340
I didn't think your mind
would be on cooking.

35:01.340 --> 35:03.618
So I made you a fish pie.

35:03.618 --> 35:05.896
Oh, thanks.

35:05.896 --> 35:07.346
That's nice of you.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.833
How are you?

35:11.833 --> 35:14.388
Uh, oh, I don't know.

35:14.388 --> 35:17.736
Just taking it a day at a time.

35:19.772 --> 35:22.120
I'm gonna speak to someone.

35:23.328 --> 35:26.779
Well, don't rush anything.
Take your time.

35:26.779 --> 35:29.472
[ Muffled talking, laughter ]

35:29.472 --> 35:31.163
[ Chuckles ]
They're getting on well.

35:31.163 --> 35:34.166
Oh, it's Jimi and Grace.

35:34.166 --> 35:36.134
Falling in love
over garden ornaments.

35:36.134 --> 35:37.307
[ Chuckles ]

35:42.519 --> 35:45.384
Oh, there's Mike.

35:45.384 --> 35:47.800
When he moved in,
I remember people saying,

35:47.800 --> 35:50.700
"Oh, no, you've got the Old Bill
watching your every move."

35:51.356 --> 35:53.358
I didn't think much of it.

35:53.358 --> 35:55.325
But now it's...

35:56.188 --> 35:58.570
I'm glad he was here.

35:58.570 --> 36:00.572
I-I'm glad you were both there.

36:02.470 --> 36:04.714
It's comforting.

36:04.714 --> 36:06.405
To think there's someone
looking out for you.

36:13.792 --> 36:15.173
Thanks, Pearl.

36:15.173 --> 36:16.312
Where to now?
Another bar?

36:16.312 --> 36:18.003
The railway bridge.

36:18.003 --> 36:19.418
A new high speed's
coming through.

36:19.418 --> 36:20.868
Oh. Right.

36:20.868 --> 36:23.250
Yeah, I'm getting into it,
the trainspotting.

36:23.250 --> 36:25.631
We get a bit of QT
while we're waiting.

36:25.631 --> 36:27.771
When it's cold, we cuddle up.

36:27.771 --> 36:29.187
You know, it's better
than what I thought.

36:29.187 --> 36:31.223
-I'm glad.
-Well, I'm glad, too.

36:31.223 --> 36:32.914
I didn't kill him
before I came to you!

36:32.914 --> 36:34.847
Keep the crazy in, Kelly.

36:34.847 --> 36:37.436
KELLY: Oh, we're past all that.
We're trainspotters.

36:37.436 --> 36:39.473
The crazy is out!

36:39.473 --> 36:40.750
[ Laughs ]

36:42.027 --> 36:44.547
Oh, look at him.

36:44.547 --> 36:45.858
So cute.

36:45.858 --> 36:48.033
But that wouldn't have
saved him.

36:48.033 --> 36:50.622
If he'd been cheating,
I'd have killed him.

36:50.622 --> 36:53.245
I would!
I'd have carved him up.

36:54.453 --> 36:55.799
Sorry.

36:55.799 --> 36:57.215
I'll see you later.

36:57.215 --> 36:59.596
[ Indistinct conversations ]

37:03.255 --> 37:04.774
[ Doorbell buzzes ]

37:10.883 --> 37:12.506
Hi.

37:12.506 --> 37:14.439
Um, Pearl brought this 'round.

37:14.439 --> 37:16.993
And, uh, it was just too much
for one person.

37:16.993 --> 37:18.512
So I thought
you might want some.

37:18.512 --> 37:20.030
I could heat it up for you.

37:20.686 --> 37:22.792
Oh, th-there's no need.
Really.

37:22.792 --> 37:24.449
MADDIE:
No, it's just --

37:24.449 --> 37:26.244
It's just to say thanks.

37:30.248 --> 37:32.250
Yeah, come in.

37:32.250 --> 37:33.423
Yeah?

37:35.253 --> 37:36.840
-Um...
-Oh, uh, kitchen's

37:36.840 --> 37:38.601
-just on your left there.
-Oh.

37:38.601 --> 37:40.119
[ Door closes ]

37:45.055 --> 37:47.437
[ Button beeps,
microwave whirring ]

37:48.956 --> 37:50.889
Sorry about the mess.
I wasn't expecting anyone.

37:50.889 --> 37:52.511
No, no, it's, um...

37:54.858 --> 37:56.032
You alright?

37:56.032 --> 37:57.861
Yeah. Yeah.

37:59.069 --> 38:01.106
-Um...
-How you doing?

38:01.106 --> 38:02.797
Oh, you know, just...

38:02.797 --> 38:04.696
good days and bad.

38:04.696 --> 38:06.284
Yeah, I know the feeling.

38:08.769 --> 38:10.288
It's just strange being at home.

38:15.741 --> 38:17.156
[ Dog barking in distance ]

38:17.156 --> 38:18.744
They're finally
getting together.

38:18.744 --> 38:21.471
MADDIE: Yeah. Falling in love
over garden ornaments.

38:21.471 --> 38:22.645
[ Mike laughs ]

38:22.645 --> 38:24.716
That's what, um,
Jimi called them.

38:24.716 --> 38:26.165
Grace corrected him.

38:26.165 --> 38:28.306
Apparently they're, um,
solar mood animals.

38:28.306 --> 38:30.066
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

38:30.066 --> 38:32.102
They were laughing about it.

38:35.347 --> 38:37.384
What, you can hear 'em
through the wall?

38:37.384 --> 38:38.385
Yeah.

38:41.388 --> 38:43.355
[ Microwave beeps ]

38:44.770 --> 38:47.221
[ Cellphone ringing, buzzing ]

38:51.190 --> 38:52.606
Hello?

38:52.606 --> 38:54.021
PEARL: I went 'round
to see Maddie earlier

38:54.021 --> 38:55.540
and I could see you
in your apartment

38:55.540 --> 38:57.093
even though the lights were off.

38:57.093 --> 38:58.336
I think she knew.

38:58.336 --> 38:59.371
I think she knew
you were watching.

38:59.371 --> 39:00.683
Yeah.
Go on.

39:00.683 --> 39:01.822
I went 'round to take her
some food, right?

39:01.822 --> 39:03.686
-Fish pie.
-PEARL: Yeah.

39:03.686 --> 39:05.550
And I could hear Grace next door
at Jimi's.

39:05.550 --> 39:08.173
You could hear everything.
Maddie must've known.

39:08.173 --> 39:10.624
She must have been able to hear
Noah when he was with Lois.

39:10.624 --> 39:13.005
She knew they were
having an affair.

39:13.005 --> 39:14.455
What if we got it wrong?

39:14.455 --> 39:16.112
We said that Noah was using
the night terrors

39:16.112 --> 39:18.494
as a cover for murder,
but what if it was Maddie?

39:18.494 --> 39:20.150
She knew you were watching.

39:20.150 --> 39:22.152
And she knew
we'd back up her story.

39:22.152 --> 39:24.362
I think she's playing us.
I'm gonna call the police.

39:24.362 --> 39:26.502
Yeah, good idea.

39:26.502 --> 39:29.021
Wait, how did you know
it was a fish pie?

39:29.021 --> 39:31.403
And why are you whispering?

39:31.403 --> 39:32.818
Mike?

39:32.818 --> 39:34.579
Don't.

39:34.579 --> 39:36.201
You don't have to tell anyone.

39:37.892 --> 39:39.411
Noah was a cheat.

39:39.411 --> 39:40.654
He -- He was a liar.

39:40.654 --> 39:42.759
He -- He was a horrible person.

39:42.759 --> 39:45.279
Y-You know about
the sexual assault accusations.

39:45.279 --> 39:46.591
He thought he could get away
with anything.

39:47.730 --> 39:50.215
-Look.
-He must've known I could hear.

39:50.215 --> 39:52.390
Not necessarily.
I mean, Jimi lived on his own.

39:52.390 --> 39:54.426
He -- He was barely there.

39:54.426 --> 39:57.395
Noah was with her next door.

39:57.395 --> 39:59.431
Next door to our home.

40:00.777 --> 40:01.847
You imagine how that felt.

40:03.815 --> 40:05.541
So don't.

40:05.541 --> 40:07.612
Just don't tell anyone.

40:09.199 --> 40:11.478
Who was on the phone?

40:11.478 --> 40:12.410
The police?

40:15.240 --> 40:16.655
Maddie, I know what you've done.

40:18.485 --> 40:19.624
[ Lock clicks ]

40:20.418 --> 40:22.143
Don't!

40:22.143 --> 40:23.697
Maddie.

40:23.697 --> 40:26.838
Maddie, put it down.

40:26.838 --> 40:28.633
Don't make this worse.

40:28.633 --> 40:29.944
[ Breathing shakily ]

40:29.944 --> 40:30.980
Maddie.

40:33.983 --> 40:34.880
Please.

40:36.434 --> 40:37.883
Maddie.

40:40.438 --> 40:41.439
MIKE:
It's alright.

40:43.441 --> 40:46.098
It's okay, it's okay.

40:46.858 --> 40:48.100
Give it to me.

40:55.453 --> 40:57.455
-I'm sorry.
-Okay.

40:57.455 --> 40:58.594
It's over.

40:58.594 --> 41:00.630
[ Sobbing ]

41:11.020 --> 41:13.609
[ Police radio chatter ]

41:17.095 --> 41:19.304
[ Indistinct talking ]

41:23.032 --> 41:24.309
You alright?

41:29.003 --> 41:30.867
It's been, um...

41:32.144 --> 41:33.767
Yeah.
It has, yeah.

41:39.117 --> 41:40.394
Thanks.

41:42.154 --> 41:44.087
[ Door opens, footsteps ]

41:46.883 --> 41:48.506
I'd better go.

41:48.506 --> 41:50.266
Yeah.

41:50.266 --> 41:52.095
-PEARL: I'll see you later.
-Alright.

41:59.551 --> 42:00.863
[ Door closes ]

42:00.863 --> 42:03.313
She saved your bacon, mate.

42:06.938 --> 42:08.733
Disarming a murderer.

42:08.733 --> 42:10.597
She's something else.

42:13.945 --> 42:15.222
Yeah, she is.

42:18.605 --> 42:20.676
Your statement can wait
till tomorrow.

42:20.676 --> 42:23.126
Get some rest.

42:23.126 --> 42:25.025
Alright.

42:25.025 --> 42:26.233
NIKKI: See ya.

42:29.547 --> 42:31.031
[ Door opens ]

42:33.551 --> 42:34.690
[ Door closes ]

42:36.036 --> 42:39.349
TOM:
So you saved Mike's life.

42:39.349 --> 42:41.420
No.
She was pretty scared.

42:41.420 --> 42:42.939
I don't think
she'd have done anything.

42:42.939 --> 42:46.218
Oh, come on. You completely
took down a killer.

42:46.218 --> 42:47.944
And you solved the case for him.

42:47.944 --> 42:49.601
Well, we did it together.

42:49.601 --> 42:51.430
Mm, no.
You're being modest.

42:51.430 --> 42:53.847
-We did.
-You figured everything out.

42:53.847 --> 42:56.435
The thin walls, the way she
could see Mike the whole time.

42:56.435 --> 42:58.161
What did he do?

42:58.161 --> 42:59.577
Apart from invite
the killer inside

42:59.577 --> 43:01.337
and nearly get himself murdered.

43:01.337 --> 43:02.752
[ Laughs ]
Yeah. You're right.

43:02.752 --> 43:04.616
-It was mostly me.
-Mm.

43:05.824 --> 43:08.862
But it's all done now, alright,
this case?

43:08.862 --> 43:10.726
The, um --
The late-night stakeouts.

43:12.037 --> 43:14.039
Yeah.
The case is closed.

43:16.697 --> 43:19.217
Do you think about it often,
being a cop again?

43:22.358 --> 43:23.980
All the time.

43:26.673 --> 43:29.158
Well, Mike ought to be worried.

43:29.158 --> 43:30.608
'Cause you'd have his job
in no time.

43:30.608 --> 43:32.644
-[ Chuckles ]
-Cheers.

43:32.644 --> 43:34.473
-Cheers.
-[ Glasses clink ]

43:34.473 --> 43:36.441
DOLLY:
I don't get it.

43:36.441 --> 43:37.960
She looks happy.

43:37.960 --> 43:40.825
[ Pearl laughs,
speaks indistinctly ]

43:40.825 --> 43:41.998
CHARLIE:
She ishappy.

43:42.758 --> 43:45.899
Tom's a-a nice guy.

43:45.899 --> 43:48.867
Just, uh, give him a chance.

43:48.867 --> 43:51.076
[ Pearl laughs ]

43:51.076 --> 43:53.285
[ Indistinct conversation ]

43:55.978 --> 43:58.014
[ Exhales deeply ]
Come on.

44:02.709 --> 44:04.642
If I was a racehorse,
they'd shoot me.

44:04.642 --> 44:06.678
[ Laughs ]
That's the spirit.

44:08.300 --> 44:10.061
